'''Kali Pradip Chaudhuri''' is an orthopedic surgeon and the founder and CEO of the [[KPC Group]], a company with interests in healthcare and related industries in both the United States and [[India]]. Chaudhuri has practiced medicine world-wide including in the United States, Canada, United Kingdom and in Southeast Asia.<ref>[http://www.voanews.com/bangla/archive/2009-07/2009-07-19-voa3.cfm?CFID=289160800&CFTOKEN=21351461&jsessionid=663049a5a215118a302a665e513c3f32756e] Dr. Kali  Pradeep Chaudhuri Speaks About His Successful Company]</ref>  Chaudhuri moved to the United States in 1980 and currently resides in the town of [[Hemet]] in Riverside County, California. 

Born in [[India]], he attended medical school at the National Medical College in [[Kolkata]], then affiliated with the [[University of Calcutta]], where he earned a Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS) and a Doctor of Medicine (MD).  He graduated in 1968 and was later certified by the American Board of [[Orthopedic]] Surgeons .  He is a [[Fellow of the American College of Surgeons]] (FACS) and Fellow of the [[American Academy of Orthopedic Surgeons]] (FAAOS), and has been acknowledged by his peers in the healthcare industry through a number of awards and accreditations.  He was the recipient of a lifetime achievement award for philanthropic contributions at the 25th Annual North American Bengali Conference.<ref>[http://tv.banglapodcast.com/?p=42 North American Bengali Convention Daily Digest - Opening Day]</ref>  The KPC Group, founded by Kali P Chaudhuri, was the Grand Sponsor of the 2009 Conference.

== Career ==
Chaudhuri had a 30-year career as an orthopedic surgeon before establishing himself as a businessman and entrepreneur in the healthcare industry.<ref>[http://www.nriinternet.com/NRIdoctors/A_USA/A_Z/C/K_P_Chaudhuri/index.htm] KPC Healthcare Services of LA starts First private medical college in West Bengal]</ref> 

He previously served as the Chairman for the Department of Surgery at the Menifee Valley Medical Center,<ref>[http://www.valleyhealthsystem.com/staff/show_speciality.php?speciality=Orthopedic+Surgery Menifee Valley Medical Center Physicians - Orthopedic Surgery]</ref> the Orthopedic Department in the Hemet Valley Community Medical Group and for the Orthopedic Department at the APEX Healthcare Medical Center. 
He is currently a member of the [[American Academy of Orthopedic Surgeons]], a preeminent provider of education in the orthopedic medical field.  He is also a member of the [[American College of Surgeons]] and the International College of Surgeons.  Further, he served as an assistant professor at the  Loma Linda University Medical School <ref>[http://www.llu.edu/llu/medicine/ Loma Linda University Medical School]</ref> in Southern California for over ten years.

Chaudhuri is also the founder and CEO of the worldwide company, '''The KPC Group'''. The company was founded in 1994 and has business portfolios in Healthcare, Pharmaceuticals, Biofuels, Information Technology, Educational Institutions, Real Estate, and Travel.<ref name="Dr. Chaudhuri Speaks About His Successful Company">[http://www.voanews.com/bangla/archive/2009-07/2009-07-19-voa3.cfm?CFID=282088082&CFTOKEN=44207766&jsessionid=8430b61e776c536ac9fb56572e67554f5374 VOA News]</ref> Through its subsidiary Integrated Healthcare Holdings, Inc. (IHHI), a publicly held company (symbol IHCH), it owns and operates a chain of hospitals in Orange County, California.<ref>[http://www.ihhioc.com/default Integrated Healthcare Holdings, Inc.]</ref>  The KPC Group and its affiliates established one of the largest Independent Physicians Associations in Southwestern Riverside County with more than 1,200 physicians.

